	1000 come to a homepage on a given day, and 600 of them click
	a link to a subpage, then you would say the site "has a 60%
	conversion rate of staying on the site after the homepage".
	Similarly, if 1000 people come to the homepage and 100 of
	those people bought a product, you'd say that "10% of site
	visitors were converted to buyers".

	Conversion rate is a common web metric to evaluate the
	performance of a site.

