	window to shrink or expand, leaving only the title bar
	visible in its shrunken state. This functionality has also
	been called WindowShade, metaphorically referring to the idea
	of pulling up window blinds.

	Collapsing the window is similar in spirit to other systems
	where a window is minimized to an icon or a text label, but
	has the advantage of maintaining the window at its current
