awareness

	[2]
	the sense of what other people are doing, even when you're
	not communicating with them directly.

	Awareness is useful for coordinating with others in
	collaborative tasks where direct communication is not always
	necessary. Awareness also refers to indirect forms of
	communication even while involved in a direct conversation,
