graceful degradation

	[202]
	the quality of a system or design such that when something
	goes wrong, it happens a little at a time and with plenty of
	opportunity to take action to correct the problem or at least
	protect against its worst consequences.

	For instance, a system that permits you to save changes to
	your currently open documents before it has to reboot because
	of a system error is more graceful than one that simply
