undo

	[207]
	the facility for reversing the effects of any given
	operation.

	Some common elaborations of undo include:

	redo facilities - for bringing back the effects of an
	operation that was undone

	repeat - repeats an operation instead of undoing it

	multiple undo - allows a user to undo a series of operations,
	not just the most recent one

	selective undo - allows a user to undo any previous operation
	without undoing everything that occurred after it

	hierarchical undo - as a user undoes some actions and
	continues with new actions, a hierarchically-organized set of
	versions is created; these versions may then be accessed and
	navigated to explore variations

	multi-user undo - in a multi-user system, several issues
	arise both from a user-interface and technical perspective,
	e.g. when a user says "undo", should the undo apply to the
	last command by the user who is undoing or should it apply to
	the last command generated by any of the users?

