	list, but also sometimes as a set of pictures, audio menus
	(for instance, in a voice-answering system), or a set of
	animations or video.

	Pulldown and dropdown menus are the common ones to see on
	computer desktops (WIMP interfaces), where they typically
	appear in menubars. They are primarily used to issue commands
	and set options.

	Menu-driven interfaces are screens with lists of options to
	guide the user to other screens. These types of menus are
	simply lists for navigation and are not typically used to
