	optimize either speed or accuracy, and they will effectively
	adopt the appropriate strategy. However, results can be
	extremely hard to compare, because time differences between a
	person who made zero errors and a person who made one error
	can be dramatic. For this reason, in situations where a
	speed-accuracy tradeoff exists, the relationship between
	speed and accuracy needs to be mapped out.

