	presentation of a rapidly-varying stimulus, such as flashing
	lights and repetitive sounds. Thus, interfaces should avoid
	strobe effects, blinking effects, and repetitive noises. In
	most interfaces, these are likely to annoy almost any user,
	but in the instances when such effects may be appropriate or
	useful to the target users, a warning should be provided,
	along with a way to disable the feature. The exact conditions
	that trigger seizure may vary, so it's even better to provide
