	%Baker's equation

	BBEE; Baker's basic ergonomic equation; an expression
	describing the factors driving the success of a particular
	assistive technology:

	Likelihood of success (S) = M/(P+C+L+T)

	where

	M = a user's motivation to complete a task

	P = the physical effort required

	C = the cognitive effort

	L = the linguistic effort

	T = the amount of time needed to activate and control the
	device

